org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen.impl
Class SimpleNeatParameters

java.lang.Object
  org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen.impl.SimpleNeatParameters
All Implemented Interfaces:
NeatParameters
public class SimpleNeatParameters
extends java.lang.Object
implements NeatParameters

Provides an implementation of the NeatParameters interface implementing all of the methods with their NEAT C++ defaults. The only operation that must be provided is the getFitnessFunction as this is implementation specific, all other values are pre-populated with default values.

Author:
Aidan Morgan

setInnovationIdsStart

public void setInnovationIdsStart(long id)
Description copied from interface: NeatParameters
Calling this allows the starting number of the innovation id's to be reset from zero, to the provided value. It is the responsibility of the caller of this method to ensure that the provided id is not already assigned to something else inside the context of this NeatParameters.

Specified by:
setInnovationIdsStart in interface NeatParameters
Parameters:
id - the id to start from.
